Hi!  I'm Lizzy!!  and I'm not Martha!!!

My personal family fan club knows that I am a cook. I've got 
just about every pot and pan known to man-even a zabaglione 
pot! So when one of my darlings finds a new one to add to my 
kitchen you can just about star the date on your calendar.

So when this new pan arrived under my tree-well, I was tickled 
pink! I got a searing pan. What makes a searing pan--you might 
ask. I am here to illuminate and tell you what the excitement 
is all about.

First of all-what is a searing pan? It looks like a large 
(12") straight -sided frying pan BUT the side is only 1" 
high. Imagine your chicken fryer only less than half as 
high. Got it?


